<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 30 at 12:09AM CST  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Talladega, northeastern Shelby and south central St. Clair Counties
through 1245 AM CST...
At 1209 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Westover, or near Chelsea, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Pell City, Chelsea, Childersburg, Wilsonville, Vincent,
Harpersville, Westover, Alpine Bay Resort, Winterboro, Alpine, Coosa
Island, Logan Martin Dam, Logan Martin Lake, Country Club Estates and
Sterrett.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
